content: A decent little RPG. I would like to say it's similar to the Atelier series in that crafting plays a big role, but crafting here ends up really only being used for creating stronger spells and spell upgrades. It also uses a time system in that you have 100 days until the game ends, and you get one of 9 endings based on how much you progressed in the plot at the end of the time. I don't like the ever-present pressure these time limits place, but it wasn't too bad here. Story is meh, but passable.

This was a mostly cute, heartwarming RPG. Pieberry is a cute & sweet witch 
girl & her storyline with the shrines, her origins, & the handsome warrior 
Justice was very endearing. Graphics are adorable. Battle system was 
decent; I liked how easy it was to level up stats if you needed to grind. 
The dialogue was amusing, but suffered from some translation issues. I also 
didn't like the "100 day" time limit for the game; it made me feel like I 
had to rush.There were also some glitches where the game would freeze up 
during the dialogue with Ralph (particularly during the magic slab request) 
& the warrior Crown (particularly after you first fight him). I ended up 
skipping dialogue to bypass the glitches, but I still managed to enjoy the 
game.

While the game is OK, there are some very bad bugs. Some of the text is not 
translated. More importantly, there are instances where the text freezes 
and will not continue, which in turn breaks the game. For example, when 
asking the merchant about his request for the second time, the text freezes 
as he describes the request to you. The other example is when going to the 
third spring, after fighting the best worrier crown, the text freezes on 
the dialog that happens afterwords which in turn makes it impossible to 
complete my game.

Ignoring the bad english translation this is a pretty fun game with good RPG elements. The story is fairly simple, following the adventures of a little Witch that can be nice, mean or neutral. The combat system is simple and easy to grasp, boss fights aren't too challenging since you can almost two shot enemies if you stack your stats correctly. The real challenge is managing the 100 days to get the full story experience without rushing towards one of the endings. Of course you can cheat and try to unlock the endings but its more fun to unlock it by playing.

content: Great game. Failed to see witch's ending, will try again. yes, few translation issues but not a big deal. I mean, you can understand what it means.   Few tips for beginners:  1. Don't stay at home and train for days. I did so for 25 days. worked my way up to 100 hp and 80 mp or so. Go out and hunt and increase stats with items. That's faster.  2. Save as much ingredients as you can and always use them for mixing in pot. Don't just eat them up (except stat increasing items) 3. Do unlock temples fast and faster. Use slowdown item a lot.  4. Dragon is strong, but not strongest. Do unlock top magic which has 7 metors (I believe you get it from 4th temple).  5. In snow map, when you meet ice golems in ice cave, use mental magic. It always works even better than fire magic, just for ice golems. (or more specifically, against heavily armored targets). I lost 10+ days trying to upgrade fire magic which didn't help anyway.  6. Do go to village. You can't, but it'll help you to advance the storyline.   Finally, for devs: please include endless mode.
replyContent: Thank you for good tips! You can play the endless mode if you get the specific ending:)  ('Continue' button is released in the end of the specific ending scene)

content: I would like to preface this review by saying that I am not a fan of mobile games, I find them to be cheap and uninspired. With that being said, I absolutely recommend this game.  I had a few dollars in Play Store credit so I decided to buy a game. I eventually chose this game because it looked cute, and no other reason. I can only say that I am very pleasantly surprised by this game. It is very fun, the story is actually pretty good, and I am very happy with my purchase.  This game's English translation is laughable at best, but I feel that adds to the charm. There are some emotional moments in the game where I would normally expect the poor translation to ruin the moment, but surprisingly it didn't.  My biggest surprise with this game was the amount of Extended Story there is after completing the game. I was expecting nothing and hoping for a New Game+, but I was very happy that the story actually extends beyond the normal end, giving me many more hours of playtime while continue to do new things and explore new areas.  All-in-all, I am very happy I played this game, and highly recommend it to anyone who wants to sit down for a few minutes, or a few hours to play an RPG.
replyContent: Thank you for your detail review and I will prepare the next game with changeless affection! :)
